        l₁(l₃(x,y,z)) + l₂(l₂(x,y),z) ± l₂(l₂(x,z),y) ± l₂(l₂(y,z),x)
        + l₃(l₁(x),y,z) ± l₃(x,l₁(y),z) ± l₃(x,y,l₁(z)) = 0

      The l₃ term is the "Jacobiator" measuring failure of the Jacobi identity.
      Signs are determined by the Koszul rule and α(i,j) factors.

